---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About · Gabriel Rubens">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">// about</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Gabriel <em>Rubens</em>.</h1>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="prose">
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ink)">
        I'm based in Portugal, originally from Brazil. Developer by background,
        Agilist for over a decade, now Product Owner by day. On the side, I
        ship products.
      </p>
      <p>
        Four of them so far: Pensio, HobbyCat, Gravity, and GotHired. I tend
        to reach for <strong>Rails, Hotwire, and Hotwire Native</strong>,
        tools built for one person to ship a lot. Postgres on the back, Kamal
        to deploy, a VPS to run it. HobbyCat is the exception, and the best
        of them: my partner concepted it and designed every visual, and I'm
        the developer on it.
      </p>
      <p>
        My thesis is plain. The internet has enough aggressive,
        attention-grabbing software. What it's short on is tools that are
        kind, tools that assume you will skip days, forget things, change
        your mind. I try to make those.
      </p>
      <p>
        If any of that resonates, or you want to say hi, I'm easy to find.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <dl>
        <div><dt>based</dt><dd>Portugal</dd></div>
        <div><dt>from</dt><dd>Brazil</dd></div>
        <div>
          <dt>stack</dt>
          <dd class="stack">
            <span>Rails</span><span>Hotwire</span><span>Django</span><span>Postgres</span><span>Kamal</span>
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div><dt>ship count</dt><dd>4 products · all live</dd></div>
        <div>
          <dt>elsewhere</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/gabrielrubens" target="_blank" rel="noopener">twitter</a> ·
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gabrielrubens" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin</a>
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>
